{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:psalms.78",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 78,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 78 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:1",
      "text": "Give ear, O my people, to my law: incline your ears to the words of my mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:2",
      "text": "I will open my mouth in a parable: I will utter dark sayings of old:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:3",
      "text": "Which we have heard and known, and our fathers have told us.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:4",
      "text": "We will not hide them from their children, shewing to the generation to come the praises of the Lord, and his strength, and his wonderful works that he hath done.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:5",
      "text": "For he established a testimony in Jacob, and appointed a law in Israel, which he commanded our fathers, that they should make them known to their children:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:6",
      "text": "That the generation to come might know them, even the children which should be born; who should arise and declare them to their children:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:7",
      "text": "That they might set their hope in God, and not forget the works of God, but keep his commandments:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:8",
      "text": "And might not be as their fathers, a stubborn and rebellious generation; a generation that set not their heart aright, and whose spirit was not stedfast with God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:9",
      "text": "The children of Ephraim, being armed, and carrying bows, turned back in the day of battle.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:10",
      "text": "They kept not the covenant of God, and refused to walk in his law;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:11",
      "text": "And forgat his works, and his wonders that he had shewed them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:12",
      "text": "Marvellous things did he in the sight of their fathers, in the land of Egypt, in the field of Zoan.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:13",
      "text": "He divided the sea, and caused them to pass through; and he made the waters to stand as an heap.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:14",
      "text": "In the daytime also he led them with a cloud, and all the night with a light of fire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:15",
      "text": "He clave the rocks in the wilderness, and gave them drink as out of the great depths.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:16",
      "text": "He brought streams also out of the rock, and caused waters to run down like rivers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:17",
      "text": "And they sinned yet more against him by provoking the most High in the wilderness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:18",
      "text": "And they tempted God in their heart by asking meat for their lust.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:19",
      "text": "Yea, they spake against God; they said, Can God furnish a table in the wilderness?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:20",
      "text": "Behold, he smote the rock, that the waters gushed out, and the streams overflowed; can he give bread also? can he provide flesh for his people?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:21",
      "text": "Therefore the Lord heard this, and was wroth: so a fire was kindled against Jacob, and anger also came up against Israel;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:22",
      "text": "Because they believed not in God, and trusted not in his salvation:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:23",
      "text": "Though he had commanded the clouds from above, and opened the doors of heaven,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:24",
      "text": "And had rained down manna upon them to eat, and had given them of the corn of heaven.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.25",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:25",
      "text": "Man did eat angels’ food: he sent them meat to the full.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.26",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:26",
      "text": "He caused an east wind to blow in the heaven: and by his power he brought in the south wind.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.27",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:27",
      "text": "He rained flesh also upon them as dust, and feathered fowls like as the sand of the sea:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.28",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:28",
      "text": "And he let it fall in the midst of their camp, round about their habitations.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.29",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:29",
      "text": "So they did eat, and were well filled: for he gave them their own desire;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.30",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:30",
      "text": "They were not estranged from their lust. But while their meat was yet in their mouths,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.31",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:31",
      "text": "The wrath of God came upon them, and slew the fattest of them, and smote down the chosen men of Israel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.32",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:32",
      "text": "For all this they sinned still, and believed not for his wondrous works.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.33",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:33",
      "text": "Therefore their days did he consume in vanity, and their years in trouble.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.34",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:34",
      "text": "When he slew them, then they sought him: and they returned and enquired early after God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.35",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:35",
      "text": "And they remembered that God was their rock, and the high God their redeemer.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.36",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:36",
      "text": "Nevertheless they did flatter him with their mouth, and they lied unto him with their tongues.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.37",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:37",
      "text": "For their heart was not right with him, neither were they stedfast in his covenant.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.38",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:38",
      "text": "But he, being full of compassion, forgave their iniquity, and destroyed them not: yea, many a time turned he his anger away, and did not stir up all his wrath.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.39",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:39",
      "text": "For he remembered that they were but flesh; a wind that passeth away, and cometh not again.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.40",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:40",
      "text": "How oft did they provoke him in the wilderness, and grieve him in the desert!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.41",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:41",
      "text": "Yea, they turned back and tempted God, and limited the Holy One of Israel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.42",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:42",
      "text": "They remembered not his hand, nor the day when he delivered them from the enemy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.43",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:43",
      "text": "How he had wrought his signs in Egypt, and his wonders in the field of Zoan:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.44",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 44,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:44",
      "text": "And had turned their rivers into blood; and their floods, that they could not drink.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.45",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 45,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:45",
      "text": "He sent divers sorts of flies among them, which devoured them; and frogs, which destroyed them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.46",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 46,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:46",
      "text": "He gave also their increase unto the caterpiller, and their labour unto the locust.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.47",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 47,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:47",
      "text": "He destroyed their vines with hail, and their sycomore trees with frost.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.48",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 48,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:48",
      "text": "He gave up their cattle also to the hail, and their flocks to hot thunderbolts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.49",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 49,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:49",
      "text": "He cast upon them the fierceness of his anger, wrath, and indignation, and trouble, by sending evil angels among them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.50",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 50,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:50",
      "text": "He made a way to his anger; he spared not their soul from death, but gave their life over to the pestilence;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.51",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 51,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:51",
      "text": "And smote all the firstborn in Egypt; the chief of their strength in the tabernacles of Ham:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.52",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 52,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:52",
      "text": "But made his own people to go forth like sheep, and guided them in the wilderness like a flock.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.53",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 53,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:53",
      "text": "And he led them on safely, so that they feared not: but the sea overwhelmed their enemies.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.54",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 54,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:54",
      "text": "And he brought them to the border of his sanctuary, even to this mountain, which his right hand had purchased.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.55",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 55,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:55",
      "text": "He cast out the heathen also before them, and divided them an inheritance by line, and made the tribes of Israel to dwell in their tents.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.56",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 56,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:56",
      "text": "Yet they tempted and provoked the most high God, and kept not his testimonies:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.57",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 57,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:57",
      "text": "But turned back, and dealt unfaithfully like their fathers: they were turned aside like a deceitful bow.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.58",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 58,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:58",
      "text": "For they provoked him to anger with their high places, and moved him to jealousy with their graven images.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.59",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 59,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:59",
      "text": "When God heard this, he was wroth, and greatly abhorred Israel:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.60",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 60,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:60",
      "text": "So that he forsook the tabernacle of Shiloh, the tent which he placed among men;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.61",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 61,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:61",
      "text": "And delivered his strength into captivity, and his glory into the enemy’s hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.62",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 62,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:62",
      "text": "He gave his people over also unto the sword; and was wroth with his inheritance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.63",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 63,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:63",
      "text": "The fire consumed their young men; and their maidens were not given to marriage.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.64",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 64,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:64",
      "text": "Their priests fell by the sword; and their widows made no lamentation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.65",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 65,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:65",
      "text": "Then the Lord awaked as one out of sleep, and like a mighty man that shouteth by reason of wine.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.66",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 66,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:66",
      "text": "And he smote his enemies in the hinder parts: he put them to a perpetual reproach.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.67",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 67,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 78:67",
      "text": "Moreover he refused the tabernacle of Joseph, and chose not the tribe of Ephraim:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:psalms.78.68",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 78,
      "verseNumber": 68,
